status_message: Abandoning everything for Jesus

American Family Association is joining countless churches, organizations, and individuals in calling for a national day of prayer and fasting on Election Eve, Monday, November 7. It is time that we, as Christians, recognize our need to repent of our own wickedness and cry out to the Lord for forgiveness - and that He might heal our broken land (2 Chronicles 7:14).

We should heed the voice of President Lincoln. He was the man who steered our nation through its greatest crisis, and he knew that God was the only one who could save us.

AFA has designated Monday, November 7, as a day when I am asking you to join me in seeking God's face. However you participate - one meal, two meals, all day - please join me and others who will be crying out for mercy.

Sign the pledge to let AFA know you will commit Monday, November 7, to a day of prayer and fasting for our nation. 

Encourage your church's clergy, your fellow church family members, neighbors, friends, and relatives to join in.

status_message: AFR Week in Review | October 28, 2016

Some Christians become so focused on what their individual calling from God on their lives are that they become paralyzed. They aren't sure what do to with their career, relationships, life that they are unable to do the things God calls every believer to do.

Wesley and TJ know that feeling. But that have each individually found that focusing on the universal callings God places on every believer has helped them find the ways God prepared for them to glorify them.

Wesley and TJ discuss on a few universal calling for believers each. Wesley focused on discipleship, family, rest, and service. TJ lists worship, love, study, and work.

These callings apply to every believer in every age of every church. But how they are fulfilled may be unique and personal.
link_name: Ep. 69 God Gives Us All Callings

Last year the AFR family provided the funding to expand a Children's Home & Orphanage for boys and girls in Southeast India. But the Indian Government has now changed the building codes, requiring totally separate facilities for boys and girls.

The government has given the ministry until September 15th to break ground on a separate Boy's Home. If they don't break ground the boys are at risk of being taken by the state and placed in a non-Christian orphanage. 

If 1000 people make a gift of $148 the funding will be in place and the ministry can break ground by the deadline.

This home for boys will be a place where even more boys can get three meals a day, attend school and learn about the love of Jesus. status_message:
A testimony from Today's Issues Miracle Monday that was e-mailed to  us. We know that God has provided oil in the past for the widow  and her sons (Second Kings 4:1-7). Why not gasoline for one of His children that asked for it? 

GOD PUMPS GAS !!!!
 
I was out of work and out of money.  Had a first interview about 9 miles up the road and thought it 
sounded like an interesting job.  When I parked the car in the driveway the gas gage was on "fumes".
So I decided that I was on foot from then on and would do in-town interviews.
 
Lo and behold, the out of town company called and wanted a second interview. My heart sank...I
didn't know if I had enough gas to get there. But I dressed and asked God for tailwinds to get me
there.  When I turned the key, the gas needle jumped up to 1/4 mark.  He didn't fill the tank, but
I had plenty to get there and accept the job offer.
 
-- 
Joyce
Sioux City, Iowa

Statement from Tim Wildmon on Dallas shooting:

Today is a day of mourning for America. Last night was the deadliest day for law enforcement since 9/11. Five Dallas police officers died and seven were wounded after one or more snipers opened fire on them near downtown Dallas. This should disturb all Americans from every walk of life to see law enforcement officers attacked by such ruthless individuals. 
Today is a day for uniting. Law enforcement officers across this nation need our support. They have one of the most difficult jobs in America. 
Dallas Mayor Mike Rawlings has called for a prayer vigil to take place today at 12PM CT in downtown Dallas. I'm asking Americans all across this country to join the city of Dallas in mourning and prayer. Wherever you are, whatever you are doing, pause for a moment to join Dallas in prayer at approximately 12PM CT.

As you plan to shop for this coming July 4th weekend, AFA urges you to avoid Target stores when making purchases.
Target's corporate policy, which allows men to frequent female restrooms and changing facilities, is a danger to women and children because it provides a possible gateway for sexual predators to gain access to their victims.

Recently a man was arrested inside a Target store for recording juvenile girls in a dressing room.

By spending your money with Target's competitors, you are letting them know that the protection of your family is more important than their bottom line. 

Will you help by doing at least one or all of the following? 

1. If you haven't already, sign the Boycott Target pledge and invite your family and friends to sign the pledge.
2. Spread the word on social media. 
3. Visit Target's Facebook page and kindly share your concerns.

For a list of other helpful resources visit www.afa.net/target
link_name: Have You Signed the Boycott Target Pledge?

Unfortunately we won't know if ti was repaired until they hang it back on the tower and turn the transmitter on. Please continue to pray for the safety of the crew that is working on the antenna. It is a twelve bay antenna that has to be hung over 500 feet from the ground on the tower. I know that's higher than most of us would want to climb. Hopefully, we will have another update for  you on Monday.

Greetings, as you continue to pray for those impacted by the storms during the week of Christmas, would you pray for us? We have a tower crew at KTXG in the Dallas/Greenville, TX area. That station will be off the air for several days as they inspect the antenna. The initial report is there is damage to it, but the crew is trying to repair it. If we have to order a new antenna it will cost upwards of $300,000. That's money that isn't in the budget. If you'd like to help us with these repairs please visit http://afr.net/donate/ 
We will keep you updated over the next several days as we learn more about the damage. At the very least, having a tower crew on site for several days will be very costly. As always, pray for the best and prepare for the worst, while trusting in our Mighty God who isn't caught off guard by this. 
Thank you for your prayers and support!

Dear Listener,
As we come to the close of this year, I wanted to let you know of a few upgrades we are making here at American Family Radio.
2015 has been one of significant advances for AFR as we continue to spread the message of Jesus Christ and biblical values across America via radio. Here are a few upgrades that are taking place:
•	We are establishing a strategic radio station in northern Virginia just outside Washington, D.C.
•	We are adding stations for the cities of Huntsville and Montgomery in Alabama. We are now covering Baton Rouge, Louisiana and adding a station in Lexington, Kentucky.

If you want to see just how effective our parent organization, American Family Association, has been this year, you can read about our numerous successful campaigns below in our report "One Thing Never Changes."

Thank you and Happy New Year,

Tim Wildmon, President
American Family Radio

Dear Friend of AFR,

The time has come. The American Family Radio Fall share-a-thon 2015 is today through October 15. Twice a year we set aside a couple of days to ask for your support.

Back in 1977 my grandfather started the National Federation for Decency out of his living room. Relying on small donations here and there, with the help of God, NFD grew into what are now the American Family Association and American Family Radio.

Every day we strive to provide you with the best Christian radio in America. We also enjoy providing our listeners with opportunities to spread the Gospel of Jesus Christ. Whether it is through Operation Tank Full of Love, Operation Christmas Child, or India Partners, we always make sure you are able to share the love of Christ through different avenues.

Reaching thousands of Americans every day with tools and information on how to restore America back to its biblical foundations is what we do here at AFA and AFR.

To donate visit AFR.net

Sincerely,
Walker Wildmon

ANNOUNCEMENT from AFR President Tim Wildmon

American Family Radio now covering ALL of Baton Rouge!

American Family Radio has broadcast its AFR Talk signal in and around Plaquemine, Louisiana, for years now. This station is 88.1 on the dial with the call letters KPAQ. Over a year ago our engineering team consulted with me and presented a plan for the KPAQ signal to reach the greater Baton Rouge area.

This was a huge door God opened to enlarge our territory.

After much thought and consulting with the board of directors here at AFR, we decided to upgrade the KPAQ signal and reach the greater Baton Rouge area. The signal went from reaching a population of 107,076 to now reaching 603,697.

This upgrade is a huge step in reaching a larger audience with the programing heard on AFR. The most important part of this upgrade is the Gospel of Jesus Christ will now reach into more households in Louisiana. Our new listeners will have access to Christian, inspirational, and informative talk radio.

None of this is possible without the faithful support of our listeners and the providence of God. I personally want to thank you for the continued support of our work here at American Family Association. We are fighting daily to restore Biblical values to America. With the help of God, we are fighting a winnable war!

Inform your family and friends that they can hear AFR Talk in and around the greater Baton Rouge area at 88.1 on the FM dial.

From Tim Wildmon
President, American Family Radio

I have good news to share with you!

About 2 1/2 months ago, I began to share with the entire AFA family about how God had provided a way for AFA to send the American Family Talk Radio signal into the highly populated areas of Northern Virginia where thousands of Washington, D.C., commuters live. You helped us to shape the message of this campaign that we named AMERICA CANNOT WAIT – a capital fundraising campaign of American Family Association. The goal was to underwrite the establishment of a new radio station in Northern Virginia to broadcast the programming of AFR Talk, the Christian conservative format of American Family Radio Network.

Since we had already spent over $1 million but needed almost another million to complete the project, I knew we could not finish this project and maintain all the other work of AFA without the help of the entire AFA family. AFA operates on a no-debt policy, so we prayed and asked our AFA family of partners, if they had the opportunity to break into the secular stronghold and powerfully speak into that Washington, D.C., corridor every day, would they be willing to make a one-time, above-and-beyond contribution to America Cannot Wait? If so, then we could fulfill that vision of expanding our radio signal in order to bring a conservative Christian voice to our nation's public policy debates.

Thanks be to God and to our faithful AFA partners!

The vision has become a reality! Over the period of 2 1/2 months, 10,634 AFA partners representing all 50 states gave generously to America Cannot Wait a total of $1,273,304.12.

The latest word from our AFR engineers is that our AFR Talk signal will be turned on around the first of November, 2015.

To God be the glory!

"Last night Aaron Klein, the bakery owner who declined to make a wedding cake for a lesbian couple, called me with the alarming news that an administrative judge had ruled that he and his wife Melissa will have to pay $135,000 to these two women for "emotional suffering." Unbelievable! The Kleins have already had to close their Oregon bakery business, Sweet Cakes by Melissa and do not have this money to pay. Aaron said it would financially ruin their family and could cost them their home. They have done nothing wrong, and their lives, along with their five children, have been turned upside down by this persecution. You can't call it anything else. This is wrong, and it's happening right here in our own country. Liberal judges and officials siding with the LGBT crowd are trying to make a point with the undeserved punishment of this family. This is America—we should have the freedom to live by our sincerely held religious beliefs. It's obvious who is really being discriminated against here.
I think we need to help the Kleins. First and foremost, continue to pray for them as this nightmare continues. Secondly, if you would like to donate something financially to help them and other Christians going through similar ordeals, click the photo below. We're all in real danger if something isn't done to put a stop to this kind of deliberate targeting and malicious treatment of Christians."
